---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Portfolio"
  description="Selected projects and work by Principal Full-Stack Engineer Eric Carlisle."
  pageType="portfolio"
>
  <p>
    Much of my work has been delivered inside enterprise environments where
    source code and internal systems cannot be publicly shared.
  </p>

  <p>
    These case studies focus on architecture, product decisions, constraints,
    and outcomes rather than implementation details.
  </p>

  <p>
    Across healthcare, digital media, retail, and platform engineering, I build
    systems that are scalable, maintainable, accessible, and useful.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Scaling Multi-Tenant Frontend Systems</h2>

  <p class="meta">
    <strong>Principal Software Engineer</strong>
    Arc XP &middot; 2018-2022
  </p>

  <p>
    Architected reusable frontend patterns and platform standards across
    enterprise publishing environments supporting many client implementations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Focused on creating systems that balanced flexibility and governance while
    improving delivery velocity and maintaining performance at scale.
  </p>

  <h3>Focus Areas</h3>

  <div class="tags">
    <span class="tag">React</span>
    <span class="tag">Component Architecture</span>
    <span class="tag">Design Systems</span>
    <span class="tag">Performance</span>
    <span class="tag">Migration</span>
  </div>

  <h3>Highlights</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Designed reusable frontend architecture patterns</li>
    <li>Supported large-scale platform migrations</li>
    <li>Improved maintainability across multi-tenant environments</li>
    <li>Bridged engineering and design system implementation</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>Reengineering Enterprise Commerce Performance</h2>

  <p class="meta">
    <strong>Senior UX Engineer</strong>
    Under Armour
  </p>

  <p>
    Led UI optimization efforts during a major site reengineering initiative
    focused on improving customer experience, delivery quality, and frontend
    performance.
  </p>

  <p>
    This engagement emphasized measurable business outcomes through architecture
    simplification, performance tuning, and experience improvements.
  </p>

  <h3>Focus Areas</h3>

  <div class="tags">
    <span class="tag">Performance</span>
    <span class="tag">UX Engineering</span>
    <span class="tag">Optimization</span>
    <span class="tag">Accessibility</span>
    <span class="tag">Delivery</span>
  </div>

  <h3>Highlights</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Modernized frontend implementation approaches</li>
    <li>Improved customer experience through targeted optimization</li>
    <li>Balanced business priorities with technical constraints</li>
    <li>Established scalable patterns for future development</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>Building Integration Layers for Product Teams</h2>

  <p class="meta">
    <strong>Full Stack Engineer</strong>
    Blue Cross NC &middot; 2024-2025
  </p>

  <p>
    Designed an integration architecture that simplified complex service
    interactions and enabled frontend teams to move faster with fewer
    dependencies.
  </p>

  <p>
    Focused on reducing system friction while improving consistency, resilience,
    and delivery confidence.
  </p>

  <h3>Focus Areas</h3>

  <div class="tags">
    <span class="tag">GraphQL</span>
    <span class="tag">Integration Architecture</span>
    <span class="tag">Feature Flags</span>
    <span class="tag">Vue</span>
    <span class="tag">Web Components</span>
  </div>

  <h3>Highlights</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Introduced service abstraction patterns</li>
    <li>Reduced complexity across upstream integrations</li>
    <li>Improved deployment confidence through controlled releases</li>
    <li>Enabled cross-framework component strategies</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>Designing Interactive Decision Experiences</h2>

  <p class="meta">
    <strong>Frontend Engineer / UX Architect</strong>
    Aspida &middot; 2025-2026
  </p>

  <p>
    Created an interactive decision experience that transformed complex
    actuarial data into an approachable and engaging user journey.
  </p>

  <p>
    This engagement combined architecture, interaction design, visualization,
    and behavioral feedback systems.
  </p>

  <h3>Focus Areas</h3>

  <div class="tags">
    <span class="tag">React</span>
    <span class="tag">State Machines</span>
    <span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
    <span class="tag">Interaction Design</span>
    <span class="tag">Animation</span>
  </div>

  <h3>Highlights</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Designed non-linear interaction flows</li>
    <li>Built resilient state management patterns</li>
    <li>Integrated animation as product feedback</li>
    <li>Balanced engagement with clarity and trust</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>How I Work</h2>

  <p>
    The common thread across these engagements is not a specific framework or
    language.
  </p>

  <p>
    I focus on identifying constraints, simplifying complexity, aligning
    stakeholders, and creating systems that help teams move faster while
    improving outcomes for users.
  </p>

  <p>
    If any of these case studies connect with the problems your team is solving,
    I'd welcome a
    <a href="/contact">conversation</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>

<style>
  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-inline);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-component);
  }

  .tags .tag {
    font-size: 0.875em;
  }

  ul {
    padding-inline-start: 1.25em;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  ul li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  ul li::marker {
    color: var(--brand-accent);
  }

  hr {
    border: none;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border-muted);
    margin: var(--space-section) 0;
  }
</style>
